{"id":"6893c73a4d85a557fd44a1769049c9b01549a90d","axis":"silent","repo":"grafana/mimir","sha":"6893c73a4d85a557fd44a1769049c9b01549a90d","parsed":{"files":[{"path":"CHANGELOG.md","lines":["@@ -20,6 +20,7 @@"," * [FEATURE] MQE: Add experimental support for splitting and caching `present_over_time` over range vectors in instant queries. #15386"," * [FEATURE] Query-scheduler: Add experimental `cortex_query_scheduler_inflight_max_age_seconds` metric reporting how long the oldest inflight request has been waiting since it was enqueued. Reports 0 when no requests are inflight. Enabled by default; can be disabled with `-query-scheduler.inflight-max-age-metric-enabled=false`. #15419"," * [FEATURE] MQE: Add support for experimental PromQL functions `min_of` and `max_of`. #15597","+* [FEATURE] MQE: Add support for the native histogram trim operators `</` (trim upper) and `>/` (trim lower). #15708"," * [FEATURE] Ingester: Add experimental early compaction of non-owned series. After a ring change, the ingester tracks series whose ownership shifted to another replica and flushes them into a block, evicting them from the TSDB head ahead of the regular head-compaction cycle. Eviction triggers when both (a) the in-memory series count exceeds the local threshold derived from `-ingester.early-head-compaction-owned-series-threshold` and the `-ingester.early-compaction-non-owned-series-min-grace-period` has elapsed, or (b) the `-ingester.early-compaction-non-owned-series-max-grace-period` has elapsed, regardless of the threshold. Disabled by default; enable with `-ingester.early-compaction-non-owned-series-enabled`. Requires `-ingester.track-ingester-owned-series` or `-ingester.use-ingester-owned-series-for-limits` to be enabled. Adds the `cortex_ingester_tsdb_early_compaction_non_owned_series_triggered_total` counter. #15314 #15653 #15657 #15661"," * [FEATURE] Ingester: Add experimental `cortex_ingester_tsdb_head_chunks_max_mmapped` gauge reporting the maximum, across all per-tenant TSDBs, of the maximum number of head chunks memory-mapped for any individual series during the last memory-mapping pass. Temporary measurement metric; will be removed once we have collected enough data. #15616"," * [FEATURE] kafkatool: Add `dump find-duplicates` command to scan an exported dump and report float samples re-sent with the same timestamp and value as the previous sample for a series. These exact duplicates are silently dropped by the ingester but still count toward received-samples metrics. An optional `--tenant` flag restricts the scan to a single tenant. #15506"],"additions":1,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"pkg/streamingpromql/operators/binops/binary_operation.go","lines":["@@ -25,6 +25,7 @@ import ("," \t\"github.com/grafana/mimir/pkg/streamingpromql/compat\""," \t\"github.com/grafana/mimir/pkg/streamingpromql/types\""," \t\"github.com/grafana/mimir/pkg/util/limiter\"","+\t\"github.com/grafana/mimir/pkg/util/promqlext\""," \t\"github.com/grafana/mimir/pkg/util/spanlogger\""," )"," ","@@ -84,8 +85,8 @@ func groupLabelsFunc(vectorMatching parser.VectorMatching, op parser.ItemType, r"," \t\t}"," \t}"," ","-\tif op.IsComparisonOperator() && !returnBool {","-\t\t// If this is a comparison operator, we want to retain the metric name, as the comparison acts like a filter.","+\tif promqlext.RetainsMetricName(op, returnBool) {","+\t\t// Comparison operators (acting as filters) and trim operators retain the metric name."," \t\treturn func(l labels.Labels) labels.Labels {"," \t\t\tlb.Reset(l)"," \t\t\tlb.Del(vectorMatching.MatchingLabels...)","@@ -685,6 +686,24 @@ var arithmeticAndComparisonOperationFuncs = map[parser.ItemType]binaryOperationF"," "," \t\treturn 0, nil, false, true, nil"," \t},","+\t// canMutateLeft is unused for the trim operators: TrimBuckets always returns a freshly copied histogram,","+\t// so there is never an opportunity to reuse the input histogram in place.","+\tparser.TRIM_UPPER: func(lF, rF float64, lH, rH *histogram.FloatHis